  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Effective treatment options for chronic myeloid leukemia (CML) or Philadelphia-positive (Ph+)
      acute lymphoblastic leukemia (ALL) patients with the T315I mutation are few. This study
      compared overall survival (OS) between CML and Ph+ ALL patients treated with ponatinib versus
      allogeneic stem cell transplantation (allo-SCT).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
